        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The V Problem</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">V has <span class="text-white font-medium">zero standard 2-letter words</span> in TWL (the North American dictionary). Compare that to X (AX, EX, OX, XI, XU) or J (JO). This means V can't be played in the tight 2-letter parallel plays that make other consonants easy to dump. V-ending words are your escape route.</p>
      </div>

